data.enText: an area where people live that is outside the centre of a city

simple_means.memory_skill: sub 接近 + urb 城市 → 靠近城市 → 郊区

tr: a residential district located on the outskirts of a city

value.def: A suburb of a city or large town is a smaller area which is part of the city or large town but is outside its centre.

example.ex: Anna was born in 1923 in Ardwick, a suburb of Manchester.
example.tran: 安娜于1923年出生在曼彻斯特的郊区阿德维克。

example.ex: ...the north London suburbs of Harrow, Barnet and Enfield.
example.tran: 伦敦北部郊区哈罗区、巴尼特区和恩菲尔德区。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: If you live in the suburbs, you live in an area of houses outside the centre of a large town or city.

example.ex: His family lived in the suburbs.
